Reviews:
These headphones have a nice design, the sound is awesome, the app is also pretty cool. I researched these headphones as much as I could before buying. In all, most reviews are pretty spot on. However, one thing that I really didn't find mentioned at all was how bad the noise cancelation is on a bus. I ride a city bus and we hit some rough roads sometimes, the noise cancelation cannot adjust to all these bumps. I thought at first the headphones I had were defective, so I contacted Sony and they sent me a new pair. Again, on the bus ride to work and home the headphones sound like crap.

Because I really do like the sound of these headphones I am deciding to keep them. These are still top notch sounding headphones and the app does help with customizing to your likes. But, I cannot give it 5 stars because of the noise cancelation issue on the bus. I also don't want to give it less than 4 because I do really like them. My bus ride isn't that long so I just decided that I would turn off the noise cancelation during my commute. So just beware if you commute on a bus and the ride is long these headphones will disappoint you and you will have to go through this 2 week process with Sony to get a new pair sent to you.

@Sony - please test these on bumpy roads and make adjustments to any future pair.
